entries.title: Jack Dorsey Says Twitter Has Too Much Power
entries.description: In a blog post after Elon Musk’s document dump, platform’s co-founder says there was no hidden agenda.

entries.title: Caroline Ellison Was Alameda CEO, But Officials Say Bankman-Fried Ran It
entries.description: Sam Bankman-Fried has tried to shift the blame for FTX’s collapse to Alameda. Regulators said it was really he who was running the crypto trading firm.

entries.title: Twitter Suspends Account That Tracked Elon Musk's Private Jet
entries.description: Mr. Musk, a self-proclaimed free-speech absolutist, had previously said he wouldn’t suspend the @ElonJet account.

entries.title: Redwood Materials Plans Battery-Materials Plant in South Carolina
entries.description: The company, run by a former Tesla executive, is accelerating its U.S. expansion, prompted in part by the Inflation Reduction Act.

entries.title: Microsoft Invests in Silicon-Battery Material Upstart
entries.description: Group14, now valued above $3 billion, also got a $100 million government grant to boost domestic battery production.

entries.title: FTX a Blueprint for Pursuing Offshore Crypto Exchanges
entries.description: The CFTC’s complaint is taking advantage of leeway granted in legislation passed over a decade ago after the 2008-09 financial crisis.
